data.description: **Back on market. Buyer financing fell through.**  Welcome to your dream home! A picturesque retreat nestled on a sprawling 1.02-acre corner lot adorned with majestic trees, lush landscaping, and an array of enticing features. Located in the Geronimo Forest Subdivision, this 4-bedroom, 3.5-bathroom, 2,324 square-foot residence is a harmonious blend of comfort and natural beauty. With lush trees, a sparkling pool, a greenhouse, and solar panels, this property embodies tranquility and modern living.    Upon entering, you are greeted by a bright and inviting living space with an open floor plan, high ceilings, and large windows that flood the home with natural light. The spacious living room boasts a cozy fireplace, perfect for gatherings with friends and family. The well-appointed kitchen, stainless steel appliances and ample cabinet space. Enjoy a quick meal or chatting with guests at the breakfast bar while enjoying the view of the trees and large yard through the windows.    Four generously sized bedrooms provide ample space for personal comfort and privacy. The master suite is a true sanctuary, complete with an ensuite bathroom featuring dual vanities, a soaking tub, and a separate shower. Two other adjoining bedrooms share another ensuite bathroom, with the office/den having a full ensuite of its own!    This property's exterior is a paradise unto itself. A sparkling pool invites you to relax and refresh during those hot Texas months, while a sprawling backyard and well-equipped greenhouse offers the opportunity for gardening enthusiasts to cultivate their own green haven. Take on your latest project in the detached workshop or just park a lawn chair under a shady tree and enjoy the moment. Imagine dining al fresco in the backyard, surrounded by the sights and sounds of nature. Embrace eco-friendly living with a state-of-the-art solar panel system. Not only will you reduce your carbon footprint, but you'll also enjoy lower energy bills and increased energy efficiency.    Situated on a generous corner lot, this property offers both space and privacy. The tranquil neighborhood is known for its friendly atmosphere and proximity to schools, shopping and dining, Government Canyon and Medina Lake. Don't miss the opportunity to make this serene oasis your forever home.    Note: Loan on solar panels is assumable. Black outlines in photos show the approximate location of the property line.  Please see survey for true property lines.
